🔍 ## Pokémon Search and Details Web App

This is a simple and interactive web application that allows users to search for Pokémon by name and view their abilities, types, and base stats using the PokeAPI.

## 🌐 Live Demo

lumecity.net (Make sure your files are deployed in public_html and named index.html!)

## 📁 Project Structure

public_html/
├── index.html         # Main HTML file
├── main.js            # JavaScript with API integration
├── style.css          # (optional if separated from <style> tag)

## ✨ Features

Responsive design using Bootstrap 5.3

Offcanvas navigation menu

Smooth scrolling with scrollspy

Search any Pokémon by name

Display Pokémon:

Image (front default)

Abilities

Base stats

Types

Error handling for invalid or empty input

## 🚀 Technologies Used

HTML5

CSS3 + inline styles

JavaScript (ES6+)

Bootstrap 5.3

PokeAPI – https://pokeapi.co/

## 🔧 How It Works

User enters a Pokémon name in the search input.

Clicking "SEARCH" triggers an API call to:

https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon/{pokemonName}

The app receives a JSON response with Pokémon data.

A styled card is dynamically created and injected into the page displaying:

Name

Image

Abilities

Stats

Types

## 🧪 Example Pokémon

Try searching for:

pikachu

bulbasaur

charizard

mewtwo

## 🛠️ How to Use / Deploy

Upload all files to your hosting provider’s public_html folder

Make sure your main file is named index.html

Visit your domain in a browser (e.g., lumecity.net)

Start searching!

